posts.name: Carlos Valenzuela
posts.cooked: Hello, we are looking for a team that could lend us a chain tensioner next week at champs. We would really appreciate the help as the one we had just broke.

posts.name: Lars
posts.cooked: You might benefit from looking into ship to pit options from both rev and andymark.

posts.name: Mike Barron
posts.cooked: Hello, what style of chain tensioner are you looking for?

posts.name: Carlos Valenzuela
posts.cooked: We don’t really have a preference wether it is spartan type tensioner or a turnbuckle both would work perfectly

posts.name: Mike Barron
posts.cooked: I will look on Monday to see if we have a turnbuckle style. I know we have never used the spartan type.

posts.name: Mike Barron
posts.cooked: Sorry I couldn’t find one today. I hope you are able to get your hands on one in Houston.

posts.name: Kevin Forbes
posts.cooked: I assume you’ll find one quickly, but if not, 1540 should have one for you over in Galileo.

posts.name: Carlos Valenzuela
posts.cooked: Thanks to both we will look for 1540 on wednesday!
